docs.abstract: The decision-making theatrics of Amazon, Facebook and other tech companies underscore the need for government to play a larger role.
docs.snippet: The decision-making theatrics of Amazon, Facebook and other tech companies underscore the need for government to play a larger role.
docs.lead_paragraph: Philadelphia spent almost half a million dollars wooing Amazon’s HQ2 campus in a 2018 competition that the company billed as merit-based. So city leaders probably weren’t thrilled to read in a new book that one of the company’s top executives frowned on its bid because he couldn’t abide the Eagles, the city’s football team.

headline.main: Companies Write Their Own Rules and Make a Mockery of Democracy

docs.abstract: In Barry Jenkins’s dreamlike adaptation of the Colson Whitehead novel, the railway is real and so is the pain.
docs.snippet: In Barry Jenkins’s dreamlike adaptation of the Colson Whitehead novel, the railway is real and so is the pain.
docs.lead_paragraph: In Barry Jenkins’s transfixing adaptation of Colson Whitehead’s “The Underground Railroad,” Martin (Damon Herriman), a white man smuggling Cora (Thuso Mbedu) as she escapes slavery, rouses her before dawn to witness something ghastly. Along the road they’re traveling, grimly called “The Freedom Trail,” the trees are hung with lynched corpses. “You need to see this,” he tells her.

headline.main: Review: ‘The Underground Railroad’ Weaves an Epic Vision
headline.print_headline: An Epic Vision of Terror and Freedom

docs.abstract: Two-thirds of characters reflect stereotypes, and just 3.4 percent of movies had leads or coleads who were Asians or Pacific Islanders, the study of 1,300 movies found.
docs.snippet: Two-thirds of characters reflect stereotypes, and just 3.4 percent of movies had leads or coleads who were Asians or Pacific Islanders, the study of 1,300 movies found.
docs.lead_paragraph: Of the 1,300 top-grossing films released from 2007 through 2019, just 44 featured an Asian or Pacific Islander character in a leading role — and one-third of the roles went to a single actor, Dwayne Johnson, a study has found.

headline.main: Stereotypes Are Rife Among Asian and Pacific Islander Film Roles, Study Finds
headline.print_headline: Stereotypes Persist for Asian and Pacific Island Characters

docs.abstract: A deal would add Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer’s 4,000 films to Amazon’s streaming library, including the James Bond, Rocky and “Legally Blonde” franchises.
docs.snippet: A deal would add Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer’s 4,000 films to Amazon’s streaming library, including the James Bond, Rocky and “Legally Blonde” franchises.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer has been in talks to sell itself to Amazon, according to three people briefed on the matter. If completed, a deal would turbocharge Amazon’s streaming ambitions by bringing James Bond, Rocky, RoboCop and other film and television properties into the e-commerce giant’s fold.

headline.main: MGM Looks to Amazon as the Hollywood Studio Tries to Find a Buyer
headline.print_headline: Amazon in Talks to Buy  MGM and Its Film Library

docs.abstract: The e-commerce giant’s European retail business had record sales in 2020, but its headquarters on the continent reported a $1.4 billion loss.
docs.snippet: The e-commerce giant’s European retail business had record sales in 2020, but its headquarters on the continent reported a $1.4 billion loss.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon had a record-breaking year in Europe in 2020, as the online giant took in revenue of 44 billion euros while people were shopping from home during the pandemic. But the company ended up paying no corporate tax to Luxembourg, where the company has its European headquarters.

headline.main: Amazon Had a Big Year, but Paid No Tax to Luxembourg
headline.print_headline: Amazon Pays No Taxes in Its European Corporate Home
